With a simple stroke
The moon and stars were no more.
Under still, windless, blackest night,
There is no thing.
A supreme void.
Charcoal crept on asphaltic canvas
Not a shimmer
Or any glimmer
To spoil its intense.
I lick the wind,
To taste the place
I only see,
In dreams
